         <abstract>
            <p>Numerical differentiation formulas of the form ∑&lt;sup&gt;N&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;i=1&lt;/sub&gt; w&lt;sub&gt;if&lt;/sub&gt;(x&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt;) ≈ f&lt;sup&gt;(m)&lt;/sup&gt;(a), α ≤ x&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; ≤ β, α ≤ a ≤ β, are considered. The roundoff error of such formulas is bounded by a value proportional to ∑&lt;sup&gt;N&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;i=1&lt;/sub&gt; |w&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt;|. We consider formulas that have minimum norm ∑&lt;sup&gt;N&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;i=1&lt;/sub&gt; w&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; and converge to f&lt;sup&gt;(m)&lt;/sup&gt;(a) as β - α → 0. The resulting roundoff error bounds can be several orders of magnitude less than corresponding bounds for high order differences.</p>
          </abstract>
